---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions | Private Chef">
  <Header />

  <main class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Terms & Conditions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Last updated: January 2026</p>

        <div class="prose sm:prose-lg max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. Service Agreement</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            By booking a private chef service through Private Chef, you agree to these terms and conditions.
            Your private chef will prepare meals in your home according to the bespoke proposal Chef Nino has agreed with you.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. Booking and Payment</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Sending a request through Private Chef is free and takes no payment. After Chef Nino reviews your request and
            agrees the details with you, he sends a secure Stripe payment link to confirm your booking. Payment is made
            only through that link; we accept major credit and debit cards.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">3. Booking Confirmation Process</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            When you submit a request, Chef Nino personally reviews it to confirm he can serve your dates and deliver the
            experience. He replies — typically within 24 hours — with a tailored proposal, the price, and a secure payment
            link. Your booking is confirmed once you complete payment through that link.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>If your dates can't be served:</strong> Chef Nino simply lets you know and no payment is taken — sending
            a request never commits you to anything.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Cancellations &amp; refunds:</strong> any cancellation or refund of a confirmed, paid booking is handled
            personally by Chef Nino, case by case. There is no automated online refund (see the Cancellation Policy below).
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">4. Service Details</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Every booking is bespoke. After you send a request, Chef Nino replies with a tailored proposal and a price built around your occasion, guest count and meals — breakfast, lunch, dinner or a buffet — as a chef day fee plus a per-guest charge by meal.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Groceries and ingredients are billed separately, at cost, and are not included in the quoted price. Service is provided in Lombardy; locations outside Lombardy are quoted on request (travel and accommodation arranged per destination, or the client provides a room for the chef).
            Your chef will arrive at agreed-upon times to prepare fresh meals in your home kitchen.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">5. Cancellation Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Cancellations made 7 or more days before service start date:</strong> Full refund minus processing fees
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Cancellations made within 7 days of service start date:</strong> 50% refund
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Cancellations made within 48 hours of service start date:</strong> No refund
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">6. Rescheduling</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Rescheduling is available at no charge with at least 48 hours notice, subject to chef availability.
            Please contact us as soon as possible if you need to reschedule your service.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">7. Client Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Clients must provide:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700">
            <li>Access to a fully functional kitchen</li>
            <li>Basic cooking equipment (pots, pans, utensils)</li>
            <li>Adequate refrigerator and storage space</li>
            <li>Clean and sanitary working environment</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">8. Dietary Requirements</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            We accommodate all dietary restrictions and allergies when communicated during booking. It is the client's
            responsibility to accurately communicate all dietary needs. We cannot be held liable for allergic reactions
            if information was not provided or was inaccurate.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">9. Service Standards</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Your chef is a vetted professional with appropriate certifications and insurance, maintaining
            the highest standards of hygiene and professionalism. The kitchen will be left clean and organized after
            each service.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">10. Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Private Chef maintains comprehensive liability insurance. We are not responsible for damage to
            client property beyond normal wear and tear during meal preparation. Any damages caused by our staff
            will be reported and resolved promptly.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">11. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            We collect and process personal information in accordance with GDPR and applicable data protection laws.
            Please see our Privacy Policy for detailed information on how we handle your data.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">12. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
            updated revision date. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of modified terms.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">13. Contact Information</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            For questions about these terms, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Email: <a href="mailto:legal@ninos-privatechefs.com" class="text-gray-900 underline">legal@ninos-privatechefs.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
